From: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 13:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] vdma: take mmap_read_lock around find_vma() for kernel >= 6.5

Kernel 6.5 made find_vma() assert that mmap_lock is held by the caller.
Without it the assertion in include/linux/rwsem.h WARN()s on every
gstreamer-fed user-pointer DMA mapping, the lookup races, and
prepare_sg_table() then fails with "failed to set sg list for user
buffer -22".

Wrap the find_vma() call with mmap_read_lock()/mmap_read_unlock() — the
same fix Hailo applied on the v5.3.0-hotfix-kernel-above-6-15 branch of
hailort-drivers, backported here so the HailoRT 4.23 driver works on
PetaLinux 2025.2 (kernel 6.12).

Signed-off-by: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
---
 linux/vdma/memory.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/linux/vdma/memory.c b/linux/vdma/memory.c
--- a/linux/vdma/memory.c
+++ b/linux/vdma/memory.c
@@ -167,7 +167,9 @@
     }

     if (HAILO_DMA_DMABUF_BUFFER != buffer_type) {
+        mmap_read_lock(current->mm);
         vma = find_vma(current->mm, addr_or_fd);
+        mmap_read_unlock(current->mm);
         if (IS_ENABLED(HAILO_SUPPORT_MMIO_DMA_MAPPING)) {
             if (NULL == vma) {
                 dev_err(dev, "no vma for virt_addr/size = 0x%08lx/0x%08zx\n", addr_or_fd, size);
--
2.43.0
